Attributes.description: Mathematical modelling of basic biological processes in ecology, physiology, neuroscience and genetics. Dynamic behavior of difference equations, differential equations, and partial differential equations, explained with reference to concrete biological examples.
Attributes.prereq: Pre-reqs: One of BIOL 301, MATH 215, MATH 255, MATH 256, MATH 258.
